<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="themes/visualrave/style/style.css"><style type="text/css"><!--.print {  color: #000000; background-color: #FFFFFF}--></style></head><body class="print" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000"><center><table border="0"><tr><td><table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><tr><td><table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="20" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><tr><td align="center"><img src="images/logo.gif" border="0" alt=""><br><br><font class="pn-title">AVI 2 VCD</font><br><font class="pn-sub">Date Sunday, July 18 @ 08:32:02 <br>Topic Velious</font><br><br></td></tr><tr><td><font class="pn-normal">This is a Freeware with which is very small and basic program, which all it does is simple AVI to VCD (MPEG1) Encoding, it can also split the encoding to fit CD sizes.<br />
<br />
Step 1 - Click on the &quot;Browse&quot; button and select your AVI Source file.<br />
<br />
<img src=crap/Encoding_-_AVI2VCD_-_Step_1.png><br />
<br />
Step 2 - If your movie is longer then your CDR capacity, use the &quot;Split Target MPEG at...&quot; option to make the MPEG fit your CD, then select your &quot;Target Format&quot; and make sure it matches your movie type.<br />
<br />
<br />
<img src=crap/Encoding_-_AVI2VCD_-_Step_2.png><br />
<br />
Step 3 - When you are done, click on the &quot;Encode&quot; button, and this will start the process, you can click on the &quot;Pause&quot; and continue encoding later as long as you don't quit the program.<br />
<br />
<img src=crap/Encoding_-_AVI2VCD_-_Step_3.png><br />
